<TITLE>BAHRAIN CINEMA BSC : Three food-themed films to be screened</TITLE>
<TEXT>
 THREE internationally acclaimed food-themed films will be screened as part of Food is Culture organised by the Bahrain Authority for Culture and Antiquities. The screenings will take place at the Bahrain National Museum auditorium today and tomorrow. Roald Dahl'sWilly Wonka and the Chocolate Factory will be shown at 5pm today. Starring Gene Wilder, this highly celebrated 1971 first adaptation of the book by the same name is now 45 years old but remains popular among children and adults alike. This will be followed by Indian film, Lunchbox at 8pm, which tells the story of a mistaken delivery in Mumbai's famously efficient lunchbox delivery system that connects a young housewife to an older man in the dusk of his life as they build a fantasy world together through notes in the lunchbox. The 2013 film was nominated for the 86th Academy Awards in the Best Foreign Film category. Italian film Mid-August Lunch, a warmly vibrant family drama and delicately balanced comedy of manners, will be screened tomorrow at 8pm. This 2008 film was adjudged Best First Film at the Venice Film Festival. All films, which will be subtitled in English and are rated PG or G, are being shown in collaboration with the Bahrain Cinema Company. (c) 2017 2016 Al Hilal Publishing and Marketing Group Provided by SyndiGate Media Inc. (Syndigate.info)., source Middle East & North African Newspapers
